<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="711" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/932: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cole</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-12T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                        1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>710. Department understands Provisional Government is urging the
                            retention at Archangel of two companies of American Engineers. If so,
                            what are your views.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>